Pre-Game Insights: Kenya has won three games while losing only two in their last five T20Is; they are coming off a 4-wicket win against Nigeria following a 14-run defeat against the same opponent.

Mozambique has lost three while winning only two games in their last five fixtures. They defeated Rwanda by 5 wickets in the previous T20I encounter. Before that, they faced three successive defeats against Botswana, Malawi, and Uganda, respectively.
Miscellaneous Highlights: The third match of the T20 WC Sub Regional Africa Qualifier B 2024 is set to take place between Kenya (KEN) and Mozambique (MOZ).
Ruaraka Sports Club Ground in Nairobi will host this clash on October 19 at 4:20 PM (IST).
Kenya is the clear favorite in betting odds, with a better recent form compared to Mozambique.
Both sides sets to play with their full-strengthen squad with no injuries reported so far.

The pitch seems to be bowling-friendly with an average of 125 runs in the last five T20s. Spinners have dominated here as compared to the pacers in the game. Rainy conditions expected, which could impact match proceedings.
